First Commit
Updates... Lots of them...
Updates... Lots of them...

Update composer details and cleanup workspace
This commit updates the name and description in the composer.json file to match the details of the new project. Additionally, several unnecessary entries from the .idea/workspace.xml file have been cleaned up to keep the workspace organized.

Update composer and tidy up workspace
This commit involves amendments to the composer.json file for alignment with the new project's details. It also includes a cleanup of redundant entries from the .idea/workspace.xml file to ensure a more organized workspace.

Add Quote, Invoice, and WorkOrder models, controllers, and policies
This commit introduces new Quote, Invoice and WorkOrder models each with their corresponding policy and controller. The models have been set to use SoftDeletes. Policies for each model define permissions for view, create, update and delete operations. Controllers for each model handle CRUD operations and the communication to these models.
Adding additional files to commit
Added lockscreen functionality

Added lockscreen functionality, updated Brand model and views, and created new client-related migrations
Made several updates in this commit, focusing on the lockscreen feature, brand model, and client-related migrations. Added lockscreen functionality to app.js and updated the Brand model with additional fillable fields. Also, created new views associated with brands and added new migrations related to the client, such as client rates and client portals. Console logs were removed from JS codes.

Expand Client model and related features
Updated the Client model to include various new relationships and fields. Additionally, added new related model, ClientRate, with associated fields. Updated the potentialClient model, the web routes, views and more. This commit greatly expands the feature set related to the client, providing deeper integration and functionality within the application.

Remove custom-switcher-P42PMXHj.js from assets
The file custom-switcher-P42PMXHj.js under the build assets was deleted. This might imply a change in the UI or interaction on the website. Check with the related UI modifications or dependencies in the project.

Update README.md and .idea workspace settings
Added project logo, badges and license info to README.md while cleaned up .idea workspace settings. This enhaces the project's visual representation and provides thorough info regarding project's status, downloads, and license, while workspace settings update ensures smoother collaboration among developers.

Improve README.md and refine workspace settings
Updated the README.md file by adding a project logo, badges, and license information to enhance its visual representation and provide comprehensive details about the project. Cleaned up the .idea workspace settings to promote improved developer collaboration.

Add middleware to route, create new models and migration files
Added middleware for view and edit routes for brands and clients to enhance permission control. Two new models, StatusSeeder and ContactDepartment, with their respective migrations files, were created to handle statuses and contact departments. Also, the generation policy from laravel-idea-personal.xml was removed and the default styles for Ckeditor were updated.

Add contact departments to admin panel
Contact departments have been added to the admin panel by creating respective routes and reflected in the side-bar. The ContactDepartmentController has been moved to the Admin folder, an index method has been added, and an index view created to present the data.

Update ContactDepartment model and related views
Updated the ContactDepartment model to allow 'name' to be fillable and added a relationship with the User model. Updated the index view under contact departments to include new layouts and functionality. Also updated several settings and configurations files including dataSources.xml and dataSources.local.xml.
